Description: UBooster is a platform for supporting college athletes, helping them to jump-start their careers.
Full Description: UBooster raises money for future college athletes to use after the completion of their NCAA eligibility after graduation. This money helps athletes jump-start their careers, further their education, or relocate in pursuit of their lifelong goals. UBooster is the world’s premier platform for supporting college athletes. Through UBooster, fans Boost funds to demonstrate their support of the choices made by high school athletes. All the funds go to a trust fund (known as a UFund) for the athletes, which they can access at the end of their NCAA eligibility. Fans have the opportunity to participate for free by using the UBooster Points they receive at signup. These points directly correlate with the athletes’ Heat Index. To keep raising an athlete’s Heat Index, fans can Boost a player while simultaneously contributing money to their UFund, which also helps their favorite athlete’s Heat Index score climb. Additionally, when fans Boost an athlete they can select which school they support and each athlete’s profile will display the leading Boosters. For example, if a fan of School U boosts Joe Football for $10, Joe Football will receive 100 UBooster Points towards his Heat Index and his profile will display School U as the leading fan-driven institution. On National Letter of Intent (“Signing”) Day, the opportunity to Boost an athlete closes. All the funds donated to these athletes will be held in escrow until his or her NCAA eligibility expires. Athletes have six years to collect their funds, starting form the time they begin their college careers.

Based upon Yogarupa's 35 years of discipleship and practice, the PYMT has elevated the standard of YTT programs.  Its unique, systematic study and experience-based curriculum leads you to Yoga's true potential as one of the most comprehensive, life-affirming spiritual tradition ever created. Students wanting to deepen their personal practice, engage in the in-depth study of ancient wisdom, or simply for the purpose of self-development may participate in ParaYoga Master Trainings.  Of course, these trainings are also available as part of a fully comprehensive teacher training program, culminating in certification as a ParaYoga teacher.   The ParaYoga Master Training Certification Program (PYCP) takes most students a minimum of 2-3 years to complete. Over the course of the certification program, you will assimilate the teachings and begin to gain true depth of skill and self mastery both as a teacher and as a practitioner. Beyond our ParaYoga Certification Program, successful completion of the 10 ParaYoga Master Trainings culminates in a 300-hour Yoga Alliance certification, which, when combined with an existing 200-hour YA certification, credentials you at the YA 500-hour level.

Full Description: iAte imports and organizes status updates from Twitter that mention restaurants.    When a tweet mentioning a restaurant is discovered, iAte's technology  analyzes the tweet and identifies the restaurant and location mentioned.  The tweet is then made discoverable on the restaurant's iAte.com page and made searchable.   At launch, iAte was adding 200,000 new restaurant tweets per month to it's system. iAte.com lets visitors see reviews, photos, and a list of trending popular  restaurants in their city.  Twitter users can also see the most popular eateries of their friends and followers and their own eating history. On Twitter, @iAte provides a way of sharing restaurant reviews only to users who opt-in to see them.  By starting their tweet with @iAte, their followers must be following @iAte to opt-in.  Any Twitter user can also get restaurant recommendations by tweeting "@iAte feedme".  iAte will reply with a restaurant suggestion based on the most popular eateries of a user's followers.
